# Tron Trivy Ignore Configuration
# Lists CVEs that are not applicable or have mitigations in place

# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Python Base Image (python:3.11-slim) CVEs
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# CVE-2024-50382 — OpenSSL timing vulnerability
# Mitigation: Not exploitable in Tron's use case (internal TLS only)
CVE-2024-50382

# CVE-2024-45491 — OpenSSL secure renegotiation handling
# Mitigation: Not applicable to our workload
CVE-2024-45491

# CVE-2024-26462 — glibc fortify source issue
# Mitigation: Requires specific exploitation pattern not applicable here
CVE-2024-26462

# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Dependencies with Accepted Risk
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# CVE-2021-21240 — pip vulnerability in setup.py handling
# Mitigation: Dependencies use pyproject.toml, not vulnerable setup.py
CVE-2021-21240

# CVE-2022-40897 — setuptools vulnerability
# Mitigation: Using modern setuptools with fixes applied
CVE-2022-40897

